; vim:ft=scdoc
# NAME

confidant.ucl - local configuration file for *Confidant*

# Synopsis

_confidant.ucl_

# DESCRIPTION

_confidant.ucl_ is read when *Confidant* is invoked, unless otherwise specified
on the command-line with *-f* or *--file*.

The format comes from *libucl*, and consists of up to three nodes

# REPOSITORY

[[ *field*
:[ *type*
:[ *default*
:[ *required?*
|  _url_
:  string
:  empty
:  *false*

# LINKS

[[ *field*
:[ *type*
:[ *default*
:[ *required?*
|  _source_
:  path
:  none
:  *true*
|  _dest_
:  path
:  none
:  mutually exclusive with _destdir_
|  _destdir_
:  path
:  none
:  mutually exclusive with _dest_
|  _type_
:  string
:  file
:  only for directory symlinks
|  _tag_
:  string
:  none
:  *false*

# TEMPLATES

[[ *field*
:[ *type*
:[ *default*
:[ *required?*
|  _source_
:  path
:  none
:  *true*
|  _dest_
:  path
:  none
:  *true*
|  _items_
:  list of paths
:  none
:  *true*
|  _tag_
:  string
:  none
:  *false*


# VARIABLES

Other than _REPO_, all of the following are determined by reading the
environment first, before falling back to the values displayed here.
All of these variables may be written fully in upper or lower case.

[[ *name*
:[ *value*
|  REPO
:  The directory your *confidant.ucl* is in
|  XDG_CONFIG_HOME
:  ${HOME}/.config
|  XDG_CACHE_HOME
:  ${HOME}/.cache
|  XDG_STATE_HOME
:  ${HOME}/.local/state
|  XDG_DATA_HOME
:  ${HOME}/.local/share
|  XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
:  /run/user/$(id -u)
|  USER
:  your username
|  HOME
:  your home directory

# EXAMPLE

```
repository: {
	url: https://codeberg.org/wreedb/config.git
}

links: {
	nvim: {
		source: ${repo}/.config/nvim
		dest: ${xdg_config_home}/.config/nvim
		type: directory
	}
}

templates: {
	home: {
		source: ${repo}/%{item}
		dest: ${home}/%{item}
		items: [
			.bashrc
			.profile
		]
	}
}
```

